text: Tore Øvrebø (born 25 August 1965) is a Norwegian rower. He competed in the men's coxless pair event at the 1988 Summer Olympics. Øvrebø has also been a rowing coach, coaching Olaf Tufte. In 2013, he became acting director of Olympiatoppen, succeeding Jarle Aambø.
